This paper involves the use of artificial neural networks (ANNs) and signal processing techniques to identify animal breeds and species based on their vocalizations. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the sub-category of Sound (cs.SD) as it deals with bioacoustics. Additionally, the use of ANNs suggests that it could also belong to the sub-categories of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Machine Learning (cs.LG), and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) as these fields often involve the use of ANNs. Finally, the paper's focus on animal identification and conservation suggests that it could also belong to the sub-category of Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) as this field often deals with applications related to biology and ecology.
